ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Visit name
log10 milliseconds reaction time
standard deviation of the log10 reaction times for each trial
arcsine square root proportion correct
number of correct responses
Total Errors
number of correct plus error moves
numberof trials presented
Form used/assessment name
Reward probability of the chosen stimulus
Notes: NULL means the reward probabilty is 0.

ElementDescription: Reward probabilities of all stimuli
Notes: The array is composed of reward probability values. Depending on the task version, the low is either 25 or 17; and high is either 75 or 83. Medium is always 50.

ElementDescription: Reward received by the subject
Notes: 0= Reward not received; 1= Reward received; 99= No payout was shown to the subject

ElementDescription: Color that the chosen stimulus changes to according to its reward payout
Notes: The color-reward association is randomized for each subject. The colors are randomly assigned.

ElementDescription: Specifies whether the chosen stimulus is from left or right
Block number within the task
Notes: -1 is practice. Generalization blocks contain compounds, learning blocks only have simple cues.

ElementDescription: Trial number within a block
Stimulus displayed on the left in this trial
Notes: The stimulus number is 0-indexed. A value of 50 means that no stimulus was displayed.

ElementDescription: Stimulus displayed on the right in this trial
Notes: The stimulus number is 0-indexed. A value of 50 means that no stimulus was displayed.

ElementDescription: Stimulus chosen by the subject
Notes: The stimulus number is 0-indexed. A value of 50 means that no stimulus was chosen.

ElementDescription: Reward probability associated with the left stimulus
Notes: NULL means the reward probabilty is 0.

ElementDescription: Reward probability associated with the right stimulus
Notes: NULL means the reward probabilty is 0.
